title.narrative: By 2022, Dominican society will be aware of and mobilized in favour of children’s rights, especially of girls.

description.narrative: UNICEF has sensitized and mobilized Dominican society through: a) public advocacy and communication campaigns, such as the one that sought f public support for the passing of the new legislation proposal that prohibits child marriage, b) the creation of platforms for the participation of adolescents as agents of change, who prepared the Adolescents´ Manifesto, read it in the media and presented it to the Vice President, and c) the strengthening of the commitment of a greater number of businesses, with 132 companies involved, some of which technically supported more UNICEF programmes, while others improved family-friendly policies and financed programme. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:04/02/2020
